uiDelete(25.10)                                                uiDelete(25.10)

Name
       uiDelete  -  Deletes  an  existing interface element with the specified
       name

Syntax
       uiDelete

       [-help]

       <name>

       Deletes an existing interface element with the specified name. If  mul-
       tiple  interface  elements  are  found  with  the  same name, the first
       matched element is deleted. Use this command to customize  the  Innovus
       graphical  interface by removing menus, menu items, and other interface
       elements that you do not require any longer.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each uiDelete parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man uiDelete

       <name> Specifies the internal  name  of  the  interface  element  as  a
              string.  An  error  is returned if an interface element with the
              specified name does not exist.

              Note: Here, <name> represents the internal name assigned to  the
              element  when  it  was  added to the interface and not the label
              that is displayed on the interface. If you specify the label in-
              stead of the name, the software will return an error.

Examples
              * The following command will delete an  interface  element  with
                the internal name <Menu1>:

                uiDelete Menu1

